les |title=Reader's Guide to Military History|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=VT7fAQAAQBAJ&pg=PA417 |origyear=2001 |year=2013 |edition=reprint |publisher=Routledge|pages=417\u201320|isbn=9781135959708 }}; evaluation of the major books\n* {{cite journal | last1 = Morgan | first1 = John | year = 2009 | title = War Feeding War? The Impact of Logistics on the Napoleonic Occupation of Catalonia | url = | journal = Journal of Military History | volume = 73 | issue = 1| pages = 83\u2013116 | doi=10.1353/jmh.0.0183}}\n* {{cite book |last=Napier |first=William  |title=The War in the Peninsula'' (6 vols) |location=London |publisher=John Murray (Vol 1), and private (Vols 2\u20136) |date=1828\u201340 }}\n* {{cite book |last=Muir |first=Rory  |year=1996 |title=Britain and the Defeat of Napoleon, 1807\u20131815}} ([https://www.amazon.com/Britain-Defeat-Napoleon-1807-1815-Rory/dp/0300064438/ excerpt])\n* {{cite book |last=Oman |first=Sir Charles William Chadwick |year=1903 |title=A History of the Peninsular War: Jan. \u2013 Sep. 1809 |volume=II |location=Oxford |publisher=Clarendon Press |url=https://archive.org/details/historyofpeninsu02oman}}\n* {{cite book |last=Oman |first=Sir Charles William Chadwick |year=1914 |title=A History of the Peninsular War: Oct. 1811 \u2013 Aug. 31 1812 |volume=V |location=Oxford |publisher=Clarendon Press |url=https://archive.org/details/historyofpeninsu05oman }}\n* {{cite book |last=Oman |first=Sir Charles William Chadwick |year=1922 |title=A History of the Peninsular War: Sep. 1 1812 \u2013 5 Aug. 1813 |volume=VI |location=Oxford |publisher=Clarendon Press |url=https://archive.org/details/historyofpeninsu06oman }}\n* {{cite book |last=Oman |first=Sir Charles William Chadwick |year=1930 |title=A History of the Peninsular War: August 1813 \u2013 April 14, 1814. |volume=VII |location=Oxford |publisher=Clarendon Press  |url=https://archive.org/details/historyofpeninsu07oman }}\n* {{cite book |last=Rathbone |first=Julian |title=Wellington's War 